<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>8 SPEED, 9 SPEED, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove boot from gear shift lever and secure assembly in vise with bottom of housing up.
                    Use a large screwdriver to twist between spring and housing, forcing spring from under lugs in the
                    housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13018f2">Figure 152</hotlnk>).
                    <emph type="bold">Do one coil at a time.</emph>
                </para>
                <figure id="f13018f2" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13018f2" filename="../figg13/G13018F2.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 152. Force Spring From Under Lugs in Housing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tension spring, washer and gear shift lever from the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13018f3">Figure 153</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13018f3" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13018f3" filename="../figg13/G13018F3.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 153. Remove Tension Spring, Washer, and Gear Shift Lever</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the spade pin from the bore in the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13018f4">Figure 154</hotlnk>). If necessary, remove the O-ring from the groove
                    inside the tower.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13018f4" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13018f4" filename="../figg13/G13018F4.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 154. Remove Spade Pin From Bore in Housing Tower</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
